  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tackling access to education issues of Rag Pickers Community</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Bridge schooling and remedial lessons 2. Drinking water and nutritional supplements 3. Support in enrolment into formal schools 4. Distribution of essential materials periodically 5. Health camps and awareness activities 6. Educational excursions 7.   Engagement and capacity building of teaching fellows 8. Hiring of bridge education centres located near the slum areas  for easy reach by children. 9. retention of fellows  and community mobilizers in both the centres</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rag pickers children do not have access to formal education and have been engaged in siblings care, sorting of garbage for earning additional income to their family.  Bridge school education provides an opportunity for these children to get enrolled in the formal education and support in providing non-formal education to the out of school children.  It is expected that children behaviour will change and education will support them in changing their life and will help them to come out of poverty.</narrative>
  </description>
